SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 63, Chapter 7, Part 1, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
63-7-131.
(a) The board shall, no later than ninety (90) days after the effective date of this
act, develop a survey to collect the following information from nurse practitioners who
have been issued a certificate of fitness from the board:
(1) The specialty in which the nurse practitioner practices;
(2) The specialty practiced by each of the nurse practitioner's
collaborating physicians;
(3) The physical address of the nurse practitioner's primary practice
location;
(4) The physical address of the primary practice location of each
collaborating physician; and
(5) How many days per week each collaborating physician is on-site with
the nurse practitioner at the same practice site.
(b) The board shall send the survey developed pursuant to subsection (a)
annually to each nurse practitioner who has been issued a certificate of fitness by the
board who has opted to receive email communications. The board may send the survey
by electronic means.
